Perennial parenting advice says one should not have favorite children, and if one does, they definitely shouldn’t ever admit it.
Does Admitting to Have A Favorite Child Soften Its Effects?
The behaviors of these parents are likely to undermine the mental health of the favorite child and to hurt those who are not favored.
Buzz Bishop, a Canadian writer and radio host, has advocated for parents to be honest with themselves and openly admit they have a favorite child.
Whether parents admit it or not, most have a favorite child, though they should heavily consider whether admitting it would be in any child’s best interest.